{"add":{"doc":{"id":"ffc139d8a466b673a5d38a7fc1198858a3b54208e77945fe198ff27bcdbebe32","url":"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/1/15/Franz_Josef_glacier.JPG/220px-Franz_Josef_glacier.JPG","previous":[],"after":["Most of New Zealand's glaciers are in the South Island. They are generally found in the Southern Alps near the Main Divide.","An inventory of South Island glaciers during the 1980s indicated there were about 3,155 glaciers with an area of at least one hectare (2.5 acres).[65] About a sixth of these glaciers covered more than 10 hectares. These include the Fox and Franz Josef glaciers on the West Coast, and the Tasman, Hooker, Mueller and Murchison glaciers in the east."]}}}